_:Nef10c061e1d74b359eeee07ecd446c68 <http://schema.org/description> "Located in London’s East End, the Museum of the Home depicts the quintessential style of English middle-class living rooms. Its collections of furniture, textiles, paintings and decorative arts are displayed in a series of period rooms from 1600 to the present day. Museum of the Home is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport ." .
